middleware_jvm_restart_portal/scripts/manage_portal.py
Start the portal

From the project folder:

python .\scripts\manage_portal.py start

Open:

http://localhost:5000
Stop the portal
python .\scripts\manage_portal.py stop
Restart the portal
python .\scripts\manage_portal.py restart
Check status
python .\scripts\manage_portal.py status
Start on a custom port
python .\scripts\manage_portal.py start --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5050

It creates logs here:

logs/middleware-jvm-restart-python.log
logs/middleware-jvm-restart-python.pid

This script runs Flask with Python directly. It does not use Gunicorn, systemd, Apache, or shell scripts.
